## This macro inverts color of black and white image in ImageJ software.
##Steps
#1. Open ImageJ, click on Process>Batch>Macro
#2. Select the input folder where black and white imagaes are stored. Select output folder where color inverted images need to be stored.
#3. Choose output format as JPEG
#4. Select 'Invert' from the drop down menu (Add macro code). This will add run("Invert"); in the box. Then click process. 

run("Invert");
